ADDIS ABABA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian police have seized 200 kilograms of cannabis in a sting operation in the central Oromia regional state, state media reported on Friday. The seizure was make in Oromia state's Shashemene, a city 250 kilometers southeast of the Ethiopian capital, Addis Ababa, Fana Broadcasting Corporate (FBC) said. Five suspects were arrested in relation to the seizure, the FBC said. The latest seizure came just one week after another catch, of 400 kilograms of cannabis, in the same city, Shashemene. Despite toughened drug laws and crackdowns, Ethiopian law enforcement have in recent years recorded an alarming increase in the number of drug busts, particularly of foreign passengers transiting through airports in the east African country.  â– 